        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1969-09-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-09-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="7"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d7">
                <head>7. Memorandum From the President’s Counsel (<persName corresp="#p_EJD1"
                        type="from">Ehrlichman</persName>) to Secretary of State <persName
                        corresp="#p_RWP1" type="to">Rogers</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d7fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName
                            corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 296, Agency Files, <gloss
                            target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>, Vol. II. No classification
                        marking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1969-09-30">September 30, 1969</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President has weighed the international and domestic political considerations
                    relating to the proposed expansion of the U.N. Building.</p>
                <p>In view of the construction moratorium and the war on inflation, he has decided
                    not to approve the funding for this project at this time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_EJD1">
                            <hi rend="strong">John D. Ehrlichman</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <note n="2" xml:id="d7fn2">Printed from a copy that bears this typed
                            signature.</note>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
